Step 1: In 12-inchnon-stick skillet, melt Becel(R) Buttery Taste margarine over medium-high heat and cook onion, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes or until tender. Step 2: Add garlic and cook 30 seconds. Stir in green beans and cook, stirring occasionally, 1 minute. Step 3: Add broth and lemon juice, then bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium and simmer 6 minutes or until green beans are crisp-tender. Season with salt and black pepper if desired. Nutritional Facts Calories (Kcals): 70 % Daily Value Total Fat: 3g Saturated fat: 0g Trans Fat: 0g Polyunsaturates: 1.0g Omega-6: 0.8g Omega-3: 0.3g Monounsaturates: 1.4g 5% 0% Cholesterol:0mg 0% Sodium:85mg 4% Potassium: 268mg 6% Total Carbohydrate: 10g Dietary Fibre: 3g Sugars: 4g 3% 12% Protein: 2g Vitamin A: 20% Vitamin C: 25% Calcium: 4% Iron: 6% Preparation Time: 10 minutes Cook Time: 10 minutes Total Time: 20 minutes http://www.becel.ca/en/becel/HeartHealthyRecipes/Side-Dishes/Savoury-Braised-Green-Beans.aspx